   <TEXT>
   <S PAR='1' RSNT='1' SNO='1'>III.</S>
   <S PAR='2' RSNT='1' SNO='2'>THE BELIEVERS' GROWTH IN LIFE</S>
   <S PAR='3' RSNT='1' SNO='3'>UNVEILED IN THE WRITINGS OF PAUL</S>
   <S PAR='4' RSNT='1' SNO='4'>The believers' growth in life is unveiled more in the writings of Paul.</S>
   <S PAR='5' RSNT='1' SNO='5'>A. Its Base</S>
   <S PAR='6' RSNT='1' SNO='6'>In the writings of the three main writers of the New Testament concerning our growth in the divine life, the base unveiled in Paul's writings is the fullest and the strongest.</S>
   <S PAR='7' RSNT='1' SNO='7'>1.</S>
   <S PAR='8' RSNT='1' SNO='8'>The Righteousness of God</S>
   <S PAR='9' RSNT='1' SNO='9'>The gospel preached by the apostle Paul is based upon the righteousness of God Rom 1:17 for God's full salvation in Christ.</S>
   <S PAR='10' RSNT='1' SNO='10'>Hence, the righteousness of God becomes the first base for the growth in the divine life of the believers, who have participated in Christ's salvation based upon God's righteousness.</S>
   <S PAR='11' RSNT='1' SNO='11'>2.</S>
   <S PAR='12' RSNT='1' SNO='12'>The Redemption of Christ</S>
   <S PAR='13' RSNT='1' SNO='13'>Christ's complete redemption Rom 3:24b is accomplished according to the requirements of God's righteousness in full and has fulfilled those requirements up to the full satisfaction of God.</S>
   <S PAR='14' RSNT='1' SNO='14'>Hence, it becomes the most solid base for Christ's redeemed people to grow in the divine life.</S>
   <S PAR='15' RSNT='1' SNO='15'>3.</S>
   <S PAR='16' RSNT='1' SNO='16'>The Justification by God</S>
   <S PAR='17' RSNT='1' SNO='17'>Based upon the complete and full redemption of Christ, God has justified all the believers in Christ Rom 3:24a; 8:30b and reconciled them all to Himself in the next item.</S>
   <S PAR='18' RSNT='1' SNO='18'>These are also solid bases for the believers in Christ to grow in the divine life.</S>
   <S PAR='19' RSNT='1' SNO='19'>4.</S>
   <S PAR='20' RSNT='1' SNO='20'>The Reconciliation to God</S>
   <S PAR='21' RSNT='1' SNO='21'>God has reconciled to Himself those whom He has justified in Christ based upon the redemption of Christ Rom 5:10a .</S>
   <S PAR='22' RSNT='1' SNO='22'>5.</S>
   <S PAR='23' RSNT='1' SNO='23'>The Washing of Regeneration</S>
   <S PAR='24' RSNT='1' SNO='24'>God has regenerated us following His reconciling of us to Himself to wash away the old creation from us Titus 3:5 .</S>
   <S PAR='25' RSNT='1' SNO='25'>Both this item and the next item are vital bases for us to grow in the divine life.</S>
   </TEXT>
